## Component Rules

### File Structure (per component file)

```tsx
// 1. Imports
// 2. Types / Interfaces
// 3. Constants (if any)
// 4. Component function
// 5. Subcomponents (if small and tightly coupled)
// 6. Export
```

### Component Template

```tsx
import { type FC } from 'react';

interface UserCardProps {
  userId: string;
  className?: string;
}

export const UserCard: FC<UserCardProps> = ({ userId, className }) => {
  // hooks first
  // derived values
  // handlers
  return <div className={cn('...', className)}>{/* JSX */}</div>;
};
```

- Always use `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts` for conditional Tailwind classes.
- Never hardcode colors or spacing values — use Tailwind tokens only.
- Use ShadCN components from `components/ui/` as the base. Wrap them in `components/common/` if you need to extend behavior globally.

