## Authentication (NextAuth.js v4)

This project uses **NextAuth.js v4** with the **Credentials provider** and **JWT sessions**. Auth config lives in `lib/auth.ts` and is consumed by the catch-all API route `app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts`.

### Auth Config (`lib/auth.ts`)

- Define `authOptions: NextAuthOptions` here and export it as a named export.
- Use `session: { strategy: 'jwt' }`.
- Extend the JWT token and session objects to carry `id` and `role` via the `jwt` and `session` callbacks.
- Never put auth logic directly inside API route files — always import `authOptions`.

```ts
// lib/auth.ts
import { NextAuthOptions } from 'next-auth';
import CredentialsProvider from 'next-auth/providers/credentials';

export const authOptions: NextAuthOptions = {
  providers: [
    CredentialsProvider({
      name: 'credentials',
      credentials: {
        email: { label: 'Email', type: 'email' },
        password: { label: 'Password', type: 'password' },
      },
      async authorize(credentials) {
        // validate credentials against DB, return user or null
      },
    }),
  ],
  session: { strategy: 'jwt' },
  callbacks: {
    async jwt({ token, user }) {
      if (user) { token.id = user.id; token.role = user.role; }
      return token;
    },
    async session({ session, token }) {
      if (session.user) { session.user.id = token.id; session.user.role = token.role; }
      return session;
    },
  },
  pages: { signIn: '/login' },
};
```

### Session in API Routes

Use `getServerSession(authOptions)` to access the session server-side:

```ts
import { getServerSession } from 'next-auth';
import { authOptions } from '@/lib/auth';

const session = await getServerSession(authOptions);
if (!session) return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
```

### Session in Client Components

Use the `useSession` hook — always guard against the `unauthenticated` status:

```ts
'use client';
import { useSession } from 'next-auth/react';

const { data: session, status } = useSession();
if (status === 'loading') return <Spinner />;
if (status === 'unauthenticated') redirect('/login');
```

### Middleware (`middleware.ts`)

The project uses NextAuth's built-in middleware export to protect all routes except auth and static assets:

```ts
// middleware.ts
export { default } from 'next-auth/middleware';

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!login|api/auth|_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico).*)'],
};
```

- Add new public routes to the `matcher` negative lookahead — never remove existing exclusions.
- Role-based guards that need finer control should be added as custom middleware logic wrapping the NextAuth export.

### Type Augmentation

Extend NextAuth types in `src/types/next-auth.d.ts` to keep `id` and `role` typed on the session:

```ts
import 'next-auth';

declare module 'next-auth' {
  interface User { id: string; role: string; }
  interface Session { user: User & { id: string; role: string }; }
}

declare module 'next-auth/jwt' {
  interface JWT { id: string; role: string; }
}
```

