## Styling Rules

- Tailwind only — no inline `style={{}}` except for dynamic values that can't be expressed as classes (e.g., CSS variables).
- Use `cn()` for conditional and merged class names.
- Responsive design: mobile-first using `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints.
- Dark mode via `dark:` variant — configured in `tailwind.config.ts`.
- Group related utility classes: layout → spacing → typography → color → interactive.

```tsx
// Good
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 p-6 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 bg-white rounded-lg hover:shadow-md">

// Bad
<div style={{ display: "flex", padding: "24px" }}>
```

