## Environment Variables

- All server-only secrets: no `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix.
- All client-accessible values: must use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix.
- Always maintain an up-to-date `.env.example` with placeholder values.
- Validate env variables at startup using a Zod schema in `lib/env.ts`.

```ts
// lib/env.ts
import { z } from 'zod';

const envSchema = z.object({
  DATABASE_URL: z.string().url(),
  NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL: z.string().url(),
});

export const env = envSchema.parse(process.env);
```

